    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The issue persists as of 1.19.1, and seems to be caused (as well) by unnecessary repetition of same arguments.\r\n\r\n```\r\n+ make install DESTDIR=/home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64 prefix=/home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr STRIP=/bin/true V=1 VERBOSE=1\r\n[...]\r\nldconfig || true\r\n/bin/sh: ldconfig: command not found\r\ninstall -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ext/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/generic/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/generic/ && \\\r\n   install -d /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/ && \\\r\n   [84KB more text]\r\ninstall include/grpc++/alarm.h /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpc++/alarm.h \\\r\n    [132KB more text] \\\r\n    /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILDROOT/grpc-1.19.1-0.x86_64//usr/include/grpcpp/ext/channelz_service_plugin.h &&  exit 0 || exit 1\r\n[  237s] make: execvp: /bin/sh: Argument list too long\r\n```\r\n\r\n(On the other hand, I do find it a little curious; I still remember that autoconf-based configure scripts would often determine that ridiculous of arguments could be given to a program - as much as 8, or even 128 MB at times. Not sure why there seems to be a limit of 128K these days..)"
